Uruguay Floats Bond for 150 Million Dollars
MONTEVIDEO , November 14 ( Xinhua ) -- The Uruguayan government has floated on the New York Stock Exchange the B Series of registered Global Bonds for 150 million U.S. dollars .
The bond has a five-year maturity period , with a fixed interest rate of 7.875 percent , it was announced here on Saturday .
The Chase Securities Bank acted as lead manager of the emission , which was registered in the United States Securities and Exchange Commission ( SEC ) .
Uruguayan Central Bank President Humberto Capote said that the conditions of the emission are " important signals " that ratify " the good performance of the country in the cautious management of its variables . "
Capote said that this is a proof of confidence of the international market in the Uruguayan economy .
